text:
Alright, give it to me straight. Are these "How I became a Software Engineer without a degree or experience" videos BS? | I know that you won't simply make a 6 figure salary from going to one measly coding bootcamp. But I have been seeing a lot of videos lately in my recommended (algorithm really must want me to be a software engineer) and they're all stories from small youtubers who talk about how they learned to code in 6 months or less and landed a job. Most of them are honest and say you won't make 6figs right off the bat. I haven't had anyone selling anything either. So I'm curious if this is realistic? Do you really not need a degree? 

&#x200B;

They speak about building experience by attending Tech Events and helping on projects. All of these are great pieces of advice. But do employers really not care about the degree aspect if you have other credentials to show for it? (Certs, experience, etc)
